<!-- NEW AUSTIN FAQS -->
<p class="accordion"><span class="question-title">Where can I find gay massage in Austin?</span></p>
<div class="panel"><span class="answer">Browse our Austin directory on gaywellness.com to find verified <em>gay massage Austin</em> therapists. Use the map and filters to compare reviews, photos, availability, and rates. Many practitioners offer both incall studio sessions and outcall to Downtown, East Austin, South Congress, Zilker, and Hyde Park.</span></div>

<p class="accordion"><span class="question-title">What is M4M massage?</span></p>
<div class="panel"><span class="answer"><em>M4M massage</em> means “male-for-male” bodywork—male massage therapists serving male clients. Sessions can be relaxation-focused (Swedish), therapeutic (deep tissue, sports), or, where permitted, sensual. Check each Austin provider’s profile for the exact services they offer and book the style that fits your needs.</span></div>

<p class="accordion"><span class="question-title">Are there gay spas in Austin?</span></p>
<div class="panel"><span class="answer">Yes. Austin has LGBTQ+ friendly spas and men’s wellness spaces offering massage, facials, body scrubs, and hydrotherapy. Look for listings near Downtown, The Domain, and South Congress. For a more social setting, some men’s saunas combine relaxation amenities with community-oriented lounges.</span></div>

